Atlas Copco has acquired S.A.S. Air Diffusion, its French distributor of compressors, the company announced in a statement. Located in St. Etienne in the southern part of France, Air Diffusion has a diverse group of small to medium-sized customers in workshops and in the manufacturing, food and beverage, wood, plastic and foundry industries. In a statement, Vagner Rego, Business Area President Compressor Technique, said, “With this acquisition we will increase our coverage in the region”. In addition, he also said it will allow them to increase their service offering and  support to their customers. The purchase price is not material relative to Atlas Copco’s market capitalization and is not disclosed.